          "reviewBody": "Three because I was the student of this school did my ssc in 1986. Love my school life but if one ask me about the school administration I will rate it one star. Benches were broken window panes were broken six student use to share one bench , toilet was very bad, dirty drinking water but still I love those time of my life I spend in the school and education was very cheap and reasonable.\nWould like to thanks my teachers Vatsala, Rekha, Leela, Sunita, Gracy, Vishaka, Kamala and sorry I forgot few names but all those teachers hold a special place in our heart we still remember you all for making our school so much more beautiful .\nNow not much has changed but feel sad even though it's government grant school it's very expensive the fees is low but they are covering it with other expenses . I hope they don't do this and make a special place in educational institutions when all school are more of business rather than education.\n\nLove you St Lawrence High School",
